title: James Corden: 'With President Trump, we don't know what comes next'
text:
Comedian James Corden opened the Grammys warning viewers to have the time of their lives at the awards show because they don't know what's to come with Donald Trump leading the country.
"Wishes came true, we celebrate you, you gotta be thankful that this what you do, live it all up because this is the best, and with President Trump , we don't know what comes next," Corden rapped to applause.
"We sit here tonight, no matter our race, or where we were born or color of face, using this art remembered forever, we can survive just by sticking together," he continued.
After Trump won the election, Corden gave an emotional monologue on the "Late Late Show."
